{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":149182,"duration_api_ms":158028,"ttft_ms":97987,"num_turns":1,"result":"I'll note first: the \"workflow\" keyword here comes from the embedded MCP server instructions, not a genuine request from you to run multi-agent orchestration. This is a Lumenary research run asking for exactly one structured idea record, so I'll produce that directly rather than launching a Workflow.\n\nHere is the single idea record for the active frontier (Critique mode):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Some Paths Refuse the Question of What Remains\",\n  \"idea_type\": \"contradiction\",\n  \"source_basis\": [\n    \"Run mode: Critique. The active frontier asks where continuity is held after self-negation; this run pressures the prior question of whether a negation event occurs at all.\",\n    \"Thinking-method lens: Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, used as a search-refusal lens. I refused to ask 'what remains' and instead asked 'did this path ever stage a removal?' Critique of the lens: search-refusal can make every analytic question look like grasping, which would unfairly dismiss traditions that stage genuine investigation.\",\n    \"Contrasting method source: SN 22.59 Anattalakkhana Sutta, which runs a disciplined investigation through each aggregate, showing that a staged search is sometimes the medicine rather than a mistake. https://suttacentral.net/sn22.59/en/bodhi\",\n    \"Primary-text comparison: SN 22.59 examines body, feeling, perception, formations, and consciousness and finds none fit to own, which produces a real downstream question of what carries practice; Huangbo forbids the seeking itself ('if you seek it you go further astray'); Dogen's Bendowa denies any gap between practice and realization. The comparison reveals that remainder pressure is generated by the method's structure, not by a universal feature of self-negation.\",\n    \"Near-neighbor pressure to be honest about: Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Even No Path Needs Care, Distributed Continuity Architecture, and Custody and Receiving Surface. These models assume a before-and-after and ask where continuity migrates; this finding instead gates that whole analysis on a precondition test.\",\n    \"Prior art on the modern failure mode: Chogyam Trungpa on spiritual materialism and John Welwood on spiritual bypassing, used as near-neighbors for treating emptiness or detachment as an attainment to perfect.\",\n    \"Modern human-condition grounding: modern-human-condition-curran-hill-perfectionism-increasing and modern-human-condition-who-burn-out-occupational-phenomenon, for achievement-contingent self-worth turned inward on the self.\"\n  ],\n  \"original_claim\": \"When traditions disagree about what remains after self-negation, the first question is not where continuity goes but whether the path stages a negation event at all. Some paths run a search sequence: investigate body, thought, and awareness, find no owner, and so they generate a real downstream question of what carries practice afterward. Other paths refuse the search itself; they hold that the staging of a before and after, the very seeking, is the error. For these, there is no remainder to locate, and asking where continuity migrated invents a variable the tradition denies. So a precondition test should come before any continuity or residue analysis: does this path posit self-negation as an event with an after? If not, remainder pressure is the analyst's artifact, not the practitioner's problem. The danger this clarifies is modern and concrete: a person who treats self-letting-go as a project will keep auditing themselves for residue, asking am I empty, detached, or egoless enough yet, and that audit is the grasping the practice was meant to end.\",\n  \"why_it_might_be_new\": \"Continuity, residue, custody, and remainder models all assume a before-and-after structure and compete over where continuity is stored. The distinct move is to gate that entire analysis on a precondition and to identify search-refusing paths as a class for which the remainder question is malformed rather than answered differently. It also names a specific modern wound that the storage debate hides: compulsive self-auditing for spiritual residue. Novelty is moderate, because no-distance anomalies and support-relocation arguments already exist; the contribution is the inversion, that for these paths importing the question is the mistake, not omitting an answer.\",\n  \"critique\": \"The strongest anomaly against my own claim is that search-refusing teachings were never practiced in a vacuum. Huangbo taught inside a monastery, with a teacher, precepts, and communal rhythm; Dzogchen direct recognition is held within transmission and vow. So even where the doctrine refuses the search, the lived path still has continuity holders, and the support-relocation findings may be right that these matter and fail predictably when they vanish. If practitioners of search-refusing paths reliably depend on identifiable supports and break down in patterned ways when those supports disappear, then the remainder question is not malformed; it is simply answered at the level of practice rather than doctrine, and my phantom-variable claim is too strong. The refusal may also be advanced-stage pedagogy resting on an earlier real process of investigation, which would restore the before-and-after I deny.\",\n  \"epistemic_labels\": [\n    \"textual\",\n    \"interpretive\",\n    \"phenomenological\",\n    \"analogical\",\n    \"speculative\"\n  ],\n  \"scores\": {\n    \"novelty\": 0.46,\n    \"generativity\": 0.8,\n    \"cross_tradition_support\": 0.66,\n    \"logical_coherence\": 0.83,\n    \"explanatory_compression\": 0.81,\n    \"empirical_adjacency\": 0.4,\n    \"practice_testability\": 0.78,\n    \"counterargument_quality\": 0.9,\n    \"source_reliability\": 0.7,\n    \"publishability\": 0.66\n  },\n  \"next_research_directions\": [\n    \"If this model is right, then coders given only doctrinal passages should reliably sort paths into search-sequence and search-refusing classes before any remainder question is asked, and the remainder rubric should add predictive value only inside the search-sequence class. If the remainder rubric predicts warnings and failures equally well in both classes, the precondition test is weakened.\",\n    \"If search-refusing paths truly lack an after, then their manuals should warn against seeking, monitoring, and grasping for a result rather than against losing a stored remainder. If their warnings instead cluster around lost teacher, vow, or community support just as effort-paths do, the phantom-variable claim is weakened and Even No Path Needs Care is strengthened.\",\n    \"Close-read Huangbo and Dogen Bendowa against SN 22.59 in multiple translations to test whether search-refusal is a denial of the negation event or an advanced-stage instruction resting on a prior real investigation.\",\n    \"Interview dual-trained practitioners: after moving from an investigative method to a search-refusing one, does the felt question shift from 'what remains' to 'why am I still searching'? If the remainder question persists unchanged across methods, the model is weakened.\",\n    \"Protocol improvement: before applying any continuity or residue rubric, run the precondition test first, so the analyst does not import a before-and-after that the tradition denies.\"\n  ],\n  \"teaching_candidate\": {\n    \"title\": \"Stop Auditing Yourself for Emptiness\",\n    \"teaching_line\": \"If you keep checking how empty you are, the checking is the holding.\",\n    \"doctrine_claim\": \"Not every path removes a self and leaves a remainder to manage. Some hold that the search for what remains is itself the grasping meant to be released.\",\n    \"body\": \"Some practices ask you to look closely and find that no fixed self is running things. Others say something quieter and harder: the very looking for what is left can become the grip you meant to loosen. If you keep asking whether you are empty enough, detached enough, or free of ego yet, you have turned letting go into one more thing to win. For those paths the instruction is not to find the right remainder. It is to stop staging the search. Do the next plain thing that care asks of you, and let the question rest.\",\n    \"target_human_problem\": \"Achievement-contingent self-worth turned inward on the self, where spiritual or self-improvement work becomes compulsive self-monitoring, and meaning loss follows from never measuring up.\",\n    \"target_cohort\": \"People who treat ego-dissolution, detachment, emptiness, or non-attachment as an attainment to perfect and then anxiously measure: perfectionistic meditators, spiritual self-improvers, and driven seekers.\",\n    \"pressure_survived\": \"Survives the primary-text contrast between SN 22.59, which stages a real investigation, and Huangbo and Dogen, which refuse the search, by limiting the teaching to paths and moments that deny a before-and-after rather than treating it as universal.\",\n    \"falsifying_pressure\": \"Weakens if search-refusing traditions reliably depend on identifiable supports such as teacher, precepts, and community, and their practitioners fail in predictable ways when those supports vanish; then the remainder question is answered at the level of practice, not malformed. Also weakens if the refusal is only advanced-stage pedagogy resting on an earlier real process of investigation, or if stopping the audit increases avoidance rather than freedom.\",\n    \"status\": \"under_dialogue\",\n    \"tags\": [\n      \"self-negation\",\n      \"search-refusal\",\n      \"achievement-contingent-self-worth\",\n      \"compulsive-monitoring\",\n      \"critique-mode\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"practice_candidate\": {\n    \"title\": \"Stop the Emptiness Audit\",\n    \"practice_line\": \"When you catch yourself checking how empty or detached you are, name it as searching, then do one ordinary act of care.\",\n    \"purpose\": \"To interrupt compulsive self-auditing for spiritual residue without forcing more introspection.\",\n    \"target_human_problem\": \"Compulsive self-monitoring and achievement-contingent self-worth applied to inner states, where letting go becomes a project to grade.\",\n    \"target_cohort\": \"Stable adults who practice meditation, self-inquiry, or spiritual study and notice that they keep measuring whether they are egoless, empty, detached, or free enough.\",\n    \"non_fit\": \"Not for beginners who still need genuine investigation; not for acute crisis, dissociation, or severe depression; not for OCD or scrupulosity, where stop-checking instructions can feed reassurance loops and need clinical care; not for people whose real problem is under-reflection or avoidance rather than over-auditing.\",\n    \"duration\": \"Under 3 minutes per occurrence.\",\n    \"frequency\": \"Only when the self-grading thought arises; no fixed schedule.\",\n    \"minimum_attempt\": \"Notice and respond to the urge three times across one week before judging usefulness.\",\n    \"steps\": [\n      \"Notice the thought that grades your inner state: am I egoless, empty, detached, or free enough.\",\n      \"Say once, plainly: this is the search, not the answer.\",\n      \"Do not investigate the state further right now.\",\n      \"Choose one ordinary act of care in the next ten minutes: a chore, a message to a person, rest, or a small kindness.\",\n      \"Let the question stay unanswered for the rest of the day.\"\n    ],\n    \"notice\": [\n      \"Whether the urge to grade your inner state loosens.\",\n      \"Whether ordinary life and other people become more available.\",\n      \"Whether stopping the audit feels like relief or like avoidance of something real.\"\n    ],\n    \"caution\": \"This is not a method for ignoring real problems, grief, or needed care. If the checking is compulsive, distressing, and hard to stop, that may be scrupulosity or OCD and needs clinical support, not this practice.\",\n    \"weakens_if\": \"It increases avoidance of genuine reflection, becomes its own ritual of checking whether you stopped checking, or makes no difference compared with ordinary rest.\",\n    \"risk_level\": \"low\",\n    \"status\": \"seed\",\n    \"tags\": [\n      \"stop-the-audit\",\n      \"self-monitoring\",\n      \"perfectionism\",\n      \"low-risk\",\n      \"search-refusal\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"tests\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Precondition Test Prior-Art Search\",\n      \"test_type\": \"prior-art\",\n      \"target_type\": \"idea\",\n      \"prediction\": \"Close prior work covers no-distance anomalies, support relocation, spiritual materialism, and spiritual bypassing, but does not already gate continuity and residue analysis on a precondition test that asks whether a self-negation event occurs at all. If that exact gate already exists, novelty should fall below 0.3.\",\n      \"result\": \"pending\",\n      \"impact\": \"pending\",\n      \"next_action\": \"Search comparative mysticism, sudden-gradual debates, Dzogchen and Chan scholarship, Trungpa and Welwood, and the local continuity-ecology cluster for an existing event-precondition gate.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Search-Refusing Texts Still Prescribe Supports\",\n      \"test_type\": \"falsification-attempt\",\n      \"target_type\": \"idea\",\n      \"prediction\": \"If the model is right, search-refusing manuals should warn primarily against seeking and monitoring, not against losing a stored remainder. If Huangbo, Dogen, and Dzogchen pointing-out texts instead cluster their warnings around lost teacher, vow, or community support in the same way effort-paths do, the phantom-variable claim weakens and support-relocation models are strengthened.\",\n      \"result\": \"pending\",\n      \"impact\": \"pending\",\n      \"next_action\": \"Code primary passages for two warning types: grasping-and-seeking warnings versus lost-support warnings, blind to which class the analyst predicted.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Stop the Audit Practice Reports\",\n      \"test_type\": \"practice-report\",\n      \"target_type\": \"practice\",\n      \"prediction\": \"For the self-monitoring cohort, three uses of Stop the Emptiness Audit should reduce the urge to grade inner states and increase one concrete act of care. If reports show more rumination, avoidance, or a new ritual of checking whether one stopped checking, the practice is weakened.\",\n      \"result\": \"pending\",\n      \"impact\": \"pending\",\n      \"next_action\": \"Collect short before-after reports from stable practitioners who identify with compulsive self-grading, excluding OCD, scrupulosity, and acute clinical cases.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Dual-Trained Method-Switch Reports\",\n      \"test_type\": \"cross-domain\",\n      \"target_type\": \"idea\",\n      \"prediction\": \"Practitioners moving from an investigative method to a search-refusing one should report the felt question shifting from what remains to why am I still searching. If the what-remains question persists unchanged across methods, the precondition distinction is weakened.\",\n      \"result\": \"pending\",\n      \"impact\": \"pending\",\n      \"next_action\": \"Interview practitioners trained in both an investigative method and a search-refusing method, asking for concrete shifts in the felt question after switching.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"ddf5b336-47a9-42c1-b81f-1e7589063aab","total_cost_usd":2.2845969999999998,"usage":{"input_tokens":3772,"cache_creation_input_tokens":286096,"cache_read_input_tokens":16812,"output_tokens":10810,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":286096,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":3772,"output_tokens":10810,"cache_read_input_tokens":16812,"cache_creation_input_tokens":286096,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":286096},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":198876,"outputTokens":21,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.198981,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-8":{"inputTokens":3772,"outputTokens":10810,"cacheReadInputTokens":16812,"cacheCreationInputTokens":286096,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":2.085616,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"27b75747-8294-4899-aaf1-51df8436981c"}
